############
Introduction
############

This version of Mayo cTAKES is an initiative of Mayo Clinic NLP Program to bring clinical natural language processing (NLP)
to end users with limited programming background in NLP. It is derived from Mayo cTAKES version 1.2.1 with project structure re-organization and some modifications to have a centralized type system and
 remove redundant codes appearing in Mayo cTAKES version 1.2.1. 
 
 #####################################################
 Sub directories included in Mayo cTAKES version 1.2.2
 #####################################################
 
 src - source folder includes source codes distributed
 auto_generatesrc - source folder automatically generated by JCan_gen for the centralized type system
 docs - documenation for each individual annotators
 lib - a collection of libraries that Mayo cTAKES is based on
 resources - resources required to run Mayo cTAKES
 testdata - shipped test data to run all annotators
 cTAKESdesc - a collection of UIMA descriptor files necessary to run cTAKES.
 
 ##############################
 Annotators available in cTAKES
 ##############################
 
Annotator's full name and file name conversions
 
clinical document pipeline - cdp
context dependent tokenizer -cdt
core - core
dependency parser - dp
dictionary lookup - lookup
document preprocessor - docpre
Drug NER - drugner
LVG - lvg
NE contexts - necontexts
PAD term spotter - pad
SideEffect - sideeffect
smoking status - smoking

##########################
Installation and Execution
##########################

To install, download distribution and unzipped the package

To execute cTAKES for a collection of documents, simply go to cTAKES installation home and run runctakesCVD.bat (runctakesCVD.sh) or runctakesCPE.bat (runctakesCPE.sh)
 which will test processable analysis engines and collection processing engines.

In Windows:
>java -Xms512M -Xms1200M -cp resources;cTAKESdesc;cTAKES-1.2.2.jar edu.mayo.bmi.ctakes.main.cTAKECVDGUI
>java -Xms512M -Xms1200M -cp resources;cTAKESdesc;cTAKES-1.2.2.jar edu.mayo.bmi.ctakes.main.cTAKECPEGUI
 
In Unix/Linux:
>java -Xms512M -Xms1200M -cp resources;cTAKESdesc;cTAKES-1.2.2.jar edu.mayo.bmi.ctakes.main.cTAKECVDGUI
>java -Xms512M -Xms1200M -cp resources:cTAKESdesc:cTAKES-1.2.2.jar edu.mayo.bmi.ctakes.main.cTAKECPEGUI

It will fire up UIMA collection processing engine (CPE) GUI. To test a specific annotator, 
go to the FILE menu and open the corresponding CPE descriptor file available in $cTAKESHOME/cTAKESdesc/.

Clinical Document Pipeline CPE file:

$cTAKESHOME/cTAKESdesc/cdpdesc/collection_processing_engine/test_cda.xml

Default:
 Analysis engine: $cTAKESHOME/cTAKESdesc/cdpdesc/analysis_engine/AggregateCdaProcessor.xml
 Test input data: $cTAKESHOME/testdata/cdptest/testinput/cda
 Test output data: $cTAKESHOME/testdata/cdptest/testoutput/cda 
 
$cTAKESHOME/cTAKESdesc/cdpdesc/collection_processing_engine/test_plaintext.xml

Default:
 Analysis engine: $cTAKESHOME/cTAKESdesc/cdpdesc/analysis_engine/AggregatePlaintextProcessor.xml
 Test input data: $cTAKESHOME/testdata/cdptest/testinput/plaintext
 Test output data: $cTAKESHOME/testdata/cdptest/testoutput/plaintext 
 

Chunker CPE file:
$cTAKESHOME/cTAKESdesc/chunkerdesc/collection_processing_engine/ChunkerCPE.xml

Default:
 Analysis engine: $cTAKESHOME/cTAKESdesc/chunkerdesc/analysis_engine/ChunkerAggregate.xml
 Test input data: $cTAKESHOME/testdata/chunkertest/testinput/cda
 Test output data: $cTAKESHOME/testdata/chunkertest/testoutput/cda 
 
core CPE file:
$cTAKESHOME/cTAKESdesc/coredesc/collection_processing_engine/SentenceDetectorCPE.xml

Default:
 Analysis engine: $cTAKESHOME/cTAKESdesc/coredesc/analysis_engine/SentenceDetectorAggregate.xml
 Test input data: $cTAKESHOME/testdata/coretest/testinput
 Test output data: $cTAKESHOME/testdata/coretest/testoutput 
 
  
Dependency Parser CPE file [NOTE, lexiconSample and sample.mod need to be created first]:
$cTAKESHOME/cTAKESdesc/dpdesc/collection_processing_engine/ClearParserCPE.xml

Default:
 Analysis engine: $cTAKESHOME/cTAKESdesc/dpdesc/analysis_engine/ClearParserTokenizedInfPosAggregate.xml
 Test input data: $cTAKESHOME/testdata/dptest/testinput
 Test output data: $cTAKESHOME/testdata/dptest/testoutput 
 
....

===============================================================
The content of README in docs is not fully reviewed. Please refer to 
<cTAKES_HOME>/README for information.

Also, some of the annotators may not have the results you expect if using the provided toy dictionaries in <c
TAKES_HOME>/resources/lookupresources. You can contact Dr. Hongfang Liu (liu.hongfang@mayo.edu) at Mayo Clini
c for resources with production dictionaries. 
 
 
